subSubSection.paragraph:
Antennae (
Fig. 3
). All antennal chaetae smooth. Ant. I with seven chaetae, Ant. II with eleven chaetae, the dorsal ones thicker and longer than ventral ones. Ant. III sensorial organ with two thick, bent ms slightly buried in a cuticular fold; guard S thinner than S1-S8 of Ant. IV, with Sgv straight and 30% longer than Sgd; and one ventral ms. Ant. IV with S1-8, 12 long “mou” chaetae, one short ordinary chaeta (i), one small subapical organ; apical bulb indistinct flat, entire, fused to Ant. IV tip.

Ocelli 2 + 2 without pigment, located on the edges of tubercle Oc (
Fig. 6
). Mandibles thin, bidentate; maxilla heads styliform. Labium long with four basal chaetae (E,F,G,f) with F very long), three distal chaetae (A,C,D) with one minute x-papilla, and three lateral chaetae (c,d,e) (
Fig. 4
). Labrum elongate, large and rounded apically, with planaria-head-like ventral sclerifications (
Fig. 5
); labral formula 0/2,4.

Microchaetae of furcal rest either present (
Fig. 10
) or undetectable. Male genital plate with 4+4 genital and 7– 12 circumgenital chaetae; female genital plate with 1+1 genital and 11–14 circumgenital chaetae.
